{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: three source collectors plus aggregation into the payload sent to summarization. A unit test of one parser would miss cross-module wiring/omission bugs. Real OS/network is not required for this behavior because source clients can be stubbed with deterministic fixtures. Higher levels rejected: behavior text is about payload completeness at the handoff, not real infra conditions, not model-output quality, and not multi-agent sequencing.","test_description":"Wire the real collection/orchestration modules with stub adapters for metrics, issue tracker, and deployment log; run one report build; assert the exact object passed into summary generation contains all three sections with expected fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is resilience/state-propagation across modules: one adapter failure must propagate as section-level fallback while pipeline continues. Unit is too low because failure appears at orchestrator-to-section rendering boundary. System rejected because unavailability can be reproduced by an in-process failing adapter stub without losing the failure mode described. Agentic rejected because behavior text requires fallback handling, not LLM judgment quality.","test_description":"Use real orchestrator/report builder with two normal source stubs and one stub raising a source-unavailable error; assert run completes, report is emitted, and the failed section is marked `data unavailable` instead of terminating.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.09,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on actual summary-generation output fidelity (whether generated narrative preserves key values). A deterministic stub would always pass and cannot detect misrepresentation/hallucination. Workflow rejected because behavior specifies one summarization outcome, not multiple sequential model decisions.","test_description":"Run the real summary-generation model on representative report inputs and evaluate whether key numeric/status values are correctly reflected in the produced narrative (with rubric or assertion checks over extracted facts).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly crosses real infrastructure boundary: end-to-end delivery to an inbox via email service/network. In-process mocks can hide real SMTP/API auth, transport, formatting, or inbox acceptance failures. Agentic rejected as minimum because this behavior's pass condition is delivery/reachability, not model-output quality; summary content can be fixed/test-controlled for this test's purpose. Workflow rejected because no multi-agentic chain is required by the behavior text.","test_description":"Execute the script as deployed against reachable test data sources and a real test email account/service; verify one run sends a full report email that is received in the configured inbox with expected subject/body envelope fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.65,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure involves real infra condition (email service unreachable) plus durability/retry across runs. A pure unit test misses cross-run state and persistence boundaries. Integration could simulate parts, but real network failure modes and run-to-run behavior are explicitly in scope; system-level execution best matches stated boundary. Agentic/workflow rejected because behavior is transport/retry durability, not model decision quality or multi-agent sequencing.","test_description":"Run the script with email endpoint intentionally unreachable; assert report is persisted to local fallback file. On the next scheduled/executed run after restoring email service, assert the saved report is retried and successfully delivered, then retry state is cleared/updated.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.27,"System":0.58,"Agentic":0.07,"Workflow":0.05}}]}
